        "title": "What Platforms are Ideal for B2B2C ecommerce?",
        "style": "light",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<p>To begin, B2B2C ecommerce is far more complex than straight up B2C. For this, you need to consider the agility of your potential ecommerce platform. Here are a few key things for B2B2C companies to consider:&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Multi Tenant Features</strong>. allows companies, distributors &amp; resellers to create sites for their end customers. This results in a very streamlined process where each party can track the total goods sold with a visibility to the revenue at various levels in the supply chain. Virto Commerce, a top B2B2C platform, offers robust multi tenant functionality. Learn more here.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Pricing Features.</strong>&nbsp;In B2B and B2B2C ecommerce, the ability to have complicated pricing structures in place is essential. Pricing function are especially useful for B2B users who have special prices assigned to them as a result of negotiated terms and agreements with the merchant. Again, Virto Commerce and other platforms designed especially for B2B and B2B2C ecommerce allow you full control on what negotiated and contract pricing you show to specific customers.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Customer Experience.</strong>&nbsp;Offering an excellent customer experience is an key way to build customer loyalty and increase revenue. B2B2C companies should focus on:&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Content:&nbsp;</strong>Make sure that messaging is consistent across channels and your store&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Usability:</strong>&nbsp;Customers expect a frictionless experience online. Does your site load quickly? Are the pages structured clearly? How easy is your site to navigate?&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Security:</strong>&nbsp;Customers are rightly concerned about security after a number of highly publicized security breaches. How secure is your site and is the level of security clearly communicated to your customers to make them more comfortable handing over their personal data?&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><strong>Mobile responsive.</strong>&nbsp;The percentage of web pages viewed on mobile continues to increase. In addition to giving your customers a seamless browsing experience when they&#39;re on the go, investment in mobile gives B2B sales reps the chance to better display your product catalog on tablets.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n",
